            <li><strong>Diwali:</strong> The festival of lights, celebrated with great enthusiasm.</li>
            <p>Diwali in Konkan is a vibrant celebration that illuminates homes and hearts with joy and festivity. The festival of lights signifies the victory of light over darkness and good over evil. Families clean and decorate their homes with colorful rangoli, lanterns, and diyas, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. Traditional sweets and snacks, such as chakli and karanji, are prepared and shared with friends and relatives. On Diwali night, people perform puja to Goddess Lakshmi, seeking blessings for prosperity and happiness. Fireworks light up the night sky, adding to the festive spirit. Communities come together for lively gatherings, singing, and dancing. The festival strengthens familial bonds and promotes a sense of togetherness, making Diwali a cherished occasion in Konkan.</p>
