    <section>
        <h2><u>Cui</u>sine</h2>
        <p>Konkan cuisine is famous for its use of fresh coconut, seafood, and spices. Signature dishes include:</p>
    </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Fish Curry:</strong> A tangy and spicy dish made with fresh catch from the Arabian Sea.</li>
            <p>Konkan is renowned for its delectable seafood, reflecting the region’s rich coastal heritage. The Arabian Sea provides a variety of fresh catch, making seafood a staple in local cuisine. Popular dishes include <b>fish curry</b>, typically made with local fish like pomfret and mackerel, cooked in a tangy coconut-based gravy infused with spices.
                <b>prawns</b> are often featured in dishes like prawn balchão, a spicy and tangy pickle, or <b>prawns masala</b>, rich with flavors. </p>
                
                <p>Crabs are another delicacy, often prepared in a spicy coconut curry or simply steamed and served with a side of garlic chutney. Bombil (Bombay duck), a unique fish, is beloved for its soft texture and is often fried or cooked in a savory curry</p>
                
            <p>Seafood is usually accompanied by rice, with coconut and local spices enhancing the flavors. The abundance and variety of seafood in Konkan not only showcase the region's culinary diversity but also highlight its deep connection to the sea, making it a paradise for seafood lovers.</p>
