            <li><strong>Puran Poli:</strong> A sweet flatbread stuffed with jaggery and lentils.</li>
            <p>
                Puranpoli is a traditional Maharashtrian sweet flatbread that holds a special place in Konkan cuisine. Made primarily from flour and a filling of chana dal (split chickpeas) mixed with jaggery, puranpoli is often flavored with cardamom and nutmeg for added aroma. The dough is rolled out thin and cooked on a griddle until golden brown, usually served with a dollop of ghee for extra richness.</p>

                <p>This delightful dish is especially popular during festivals like Gudi Padwa and Diwali, symbolizing celebration and joy. It is often enjoyed with a side of milk or a sweetened beverage. Puranpoli is not only cherished for its taste but also for its cultural significance, representing the warmth of home-cooked meals and festive gatherings in Konkan.</p>
