                <li><strong>Sol Kadhi:</strong> A refreshing drink made fr4m coconut milk and kokum.</li>
                <p>Sol Kadhi is a refreshing and tangy drink from the Konkan region, celebrated for its unique flavor and cooling properties. Made from coconut milk and kokum (a tropical fruit), this vibrant pink beverage is often enjoyed as an accompaniment to meals or as a soothing refreshment on hot days.</p>
                
                <p>To prepare Sol Kadhi, kokum is soaked in water, releasing its tangy flavor and rich color. The extracted kokum juice is then mixed with creamy coconut milk, seasoned with spices like cumin, green chilies, and a pinch of salt. Some variations may include garnishing with fresh coriander or garlic for added depth</p>
