            <p></p>
            
            <li><strong>Mural painting :</strong> A tribal art form characterized by simple geometric shapes.</li>
            <p>
                Mural painting in Konkan is a vibrant and expressive art form that adorns the walls of temples, homes, and public spaces, reflecting the region's rich cultural heritage. These murals often depict mythological themes, local legends, and religious narratives, bringing stories to life with vivid colors and intricate details. Artists traditionally used natural pigments derived from plants and minerals, creating a distinctive aesthetic that connects deeply with the environmen</p>
                <p>The murals serve not only as decoration but also as a means of preserving cultural identity and history, often illustrating the daily lives and beliefs of the communities. Techniques vary from detailed storytelling scenes to abstract designs, each carrying symbolic meanings. In recent years, mural painting has experienced a revival, with contemporary artists incorporating traditional motifs into modern contexts, bridging the past and present. This art form remains a vital part of Konkan's cultural landscape, captivating viewers and enriching the region’s artistic legacy.</p>
